value.title: Biden calls for 'commonsense gun law reforms' on anniversary of Parkland shooting
value.excerpt: President Biden called on Congress to pass "commonsense gun law reforms" on Sunday in a message marking the third anniversary of the shooting at Marjory Stoneman Douglas High School in Parkland, Fla.

value.title: Trump triumphant – but senior Republicans still see battles ahead

value.title: Biden order reestablishes faith-focused White House office
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden has signed an executive order relaunching a White House office aimed at fostering cooperation between the federal government and faith-based and secular community organizations

value.title: GOP Gov. Larry Hogan Urges Party to Leave 'Cult of Donald Trump,' Hails Conviction Votes

value.title: Black immigrant advocates praise Biden for reinstating deportation protections for Liberians who fled civil war
value.excerpt: More than 10,000 Liberians, who have been living in the U.S. without legal status since fleeing a civil war decades ago, will get to stay for now.

value.title: Gov. governor: Trump's final chapter hasn't been written
value.excerpt: Republican Gov. Larry Hogan of Maryland tells CNN's Jake Tapper he thinks the final chapter of Donald Trump and where the Republican party goes hasn't been written yet.

value.title: Graham: McConnell 'put a load on Republicans' back' with anti-Trump speech
value.excerpt: Sen. Lindsey Graham, R-S.C., called out Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell for speaking out against former President Donald Trump after voting to acquit Trump at his impeachment trial.

value.title: Trump impeachment trial: Biden warns democracy is fragile
value.excerpt: US President Joe Biden has called his predecessor Donald Trump's acquittal for inciting mob violence a reminder that "democracy is fragile". A majority of senators voted to convict Mr Trump but the numbers fell short of the two-thirds required to do so.

value.excerpt: President Joe Biden is responding to the acquittal of Donald Trump by stating that all Americans, especially the nation’s leaders, have a duty and responsibility “to defend the truth and to defeat the lies.

value.title: Rep. Jaime Herrera Beutler would have 'testified under oath' if subpoenaed at Trump impeachment trial, spokesman says
value.excerpt: "She’s already offered all the information she has, and she would have testified under oath," Rep. Jaime Herrera Beutler's office said.

value.title: Trump attorney rips off mic after questioning from CBSN anchor
value.excerpt: The Senate voted Saturday to acquit former President Donald Trump on a charge of inciting the January 6th insurrection at the Capitol. Following the vote, defense attorney Michael van der Veen joined CBSN's Lana Zak to discuss the trial in a sometimes contentious interview.

value.title: Biden says 'democracy must always be defended' after Trump's acquittal in second impeachment trial
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden weighed in late Saturday night on former President Donald Trump's acquittal in his second impeachment trial, saying that democracy is "fragile" and "must always be defended."

value.title: Fact check: Trump lawyer closes impeachment defense with a barrage of dishonesty
value.excerpt: Former President Donald Trump's impeachment defense was dishonest from start to finish.

value.title: McConnell blames Trump but voted not guilty anyway
value.excerpt: Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell has told his colleagues that he will vote to acquit former President Donald Trump of inciting the insurrection at the US Capitol last month, according to a source familiar with the conversations.

value.title: Home of Trump attorney Michael van der Veen vandalized
value.excerpt: The home of Trump defense attorney Michael van der Veen was vandalized Friday night.

value.title: The ‘Disgraceful Acquittal’ of Donald Trump
value.excerpt: A sad, sad day for democracy,” one reader writes. “It was craven cowardice for Republicans to put Mr. Trump before country,” writes another.

value.title: Trump was aware Pence had been evacuated to secure location as rioters stormed Capitol
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump was aware his vice president had been evacuated to a secure location as rioters stormed the US Capitol, according to a person who was with Trump on January 6.

value.title: Pence's former chief of staff has been contacted about providing information in impeachment trial
value.excerpt: Marc Short, former Vice President Mike Pence's chief of staff, has been contacted about providing information to House impeachment managers about threats to Pence during last month's Capitol riot, a source familiar with the matter tells CNN.

value.title: Biden administration expresses 'deep concerns' about WHO's China probe
value.excerpt: The Biden administration on Saturday expressed "deep concerns" about the World Health Organization’s (WHO) probe into the Chinese handling of the coronavirus.
